==Description== <!--T:3-->

<!--T:4-->
The [[Image:Curves_JoinCurve.svg|24px]] [[Curves_JoinCurve|Curves JoinCurve]] joins the selected edges into BSpline curves. This tool is part of the [[External_workbenches|external workbench]] called [[Curves_Workbench|Curves]].

<!--T:12-->
[[File:JoinCurve_pic1.jpg|600px]]

==Usage== <!--T:5-->

<!--T:6-->
# Switch to the [[Image:Curves_workbench_icon.svg|24px]] [[Curves_Workbench|Curves]] workbench (install from [[Image:Std_AddonMgr.svg|24px]] [[Std_AddonMgr|Addon Manager]] is necessary, if not previously installed)
# Select one or several edges in [[3D_view|3D view]]. (use the CTRL key for several selection)
# Edges must be added in a consecutive order. And be selected from sketch, any shape's edge.
# Invoke the Curves JoinCurve command several ways
#* Press the [[Image:Curves_JoinCurve.svg|24px]] button
#* Use the {{MenuCommand|Curves → Join Curves}}
# All edges are merged to a single one Bspline. 

